The National Security Advisors of the United States, Japan, and the Philippines held a phone call to discuss their commitment to freedom of navigation and international law in the South China Sea and East China Sea. They expressed concerns about China's recent actions near Second Thomas Shoal and Scarborough Reef and called on China to abide by a 2016 ruling and cease further provocative behavior. The United States reaffirmed its alliance commitments to Japan and the Philippines. The three countries emphasized the importance of trilateral cooperation in areas such as defense, cybersecurity, maritime order, humanitarian assistance, disaster relief, and economic order. They also agreed to coordinate closely in the coming months to promote a free and open Indo-Pacific.